      <div class="msgContentFrame">I hate to bring opportunity cost into a discussion like this, but you might also want to consider the value of the shards.  Unless you're a dedicated purist who refuses to buy anything at all to level their crafting, sooner or later you're going to be buying shards or you're going to be leveling <b>extremely</b> slow once you get to about the rank 15 range, and your adventures will all but grind to a halt once you hit rank 20.  I understand the point you're making and I'm not implying that I think it's bad advice, I just want to throw in the shard issue, because that's emerging as the true hidden cost in all crafting. <br /> <br />Also, you don't need to buy copper nuggets.  It's a rank 1 goldsmithing synth from yellow copper ore that turns four ore into 12 nuggets. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct  9th 2010  2:53am by Aurelius </span></i></div>
