      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Vidffxiv wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig">Also, you don't need to buy copper nuggets. It's a rank 1 goldsmithing synth from yellow copper ore that turns four ore into 12 nuggets.</div></div> <br /> <br />Which will cost you 1 Fire CRYSTAL each, not a Shard =\</div></div> <br /> <br />One fire crystal sells for typically 1500-2000gil on my server because those (along with earth crystals) are the most frequent ones to drop, especially in Thanalan.  Which means you can also get them for free if you farm them around Thanalan.  There's nowhere to farm copper nuggets.  You either buy them (400g x 12 = 4800g...double or more the price of a fire crystal) or you make them (&quot;free&quot; if you farm the crystals) and hey, it's goldsmithing skill points which help towards ranking up so you can make silver nuggets and ingots.  Silver ingots can be used to make silver wire, and silver wire can be used to make silver rings.  Both synths will net armorer skill points in the rank 25+ range. <br /> <br />I only brought it up because if the goal is to say &quot;free&quot;, then we'd probably want to look at all possible avenues.  Farming crystals and thwacking coblyns or mining for ore can keep it not only free but profitable if you exclude opportunity cost, which you'd have to do in order to call your initial idea free anyways because if you added in shard cost to your example, you'd still be running a loss.</div>
